The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 Johannesburg, June 22: Telecom firms Bharti Airtel and R-Com have joined the race to acquire the African business of Kuwait-based Zain Group, South Africas newspaper BusinessDay has reported. The two firms have joined French company Vivendi, which is still locked in discussions with the Kuwait group for a business valued at $12 billion, the report said.                            
	 Mumbai, June 22: Tech Mahindra managing director Vineet Nayyar has made Rs 11.20 crore by offloading 1.45 lakh shares of the firm in three tranches. The promoters of Dr Reddys Laboratories, Dr Reddys Holdings and K. Anji Reddy have sold shares of the firm worth Rs 69.99 crore through open market transactions.                            
	 New Delhi, June 22: Accounting regulator ICAI has asked all chartered accounting firms with foreign tie-ups to furnish details of their contracts and income tax assessment orders for the last three years to the high powered committee.                            
	 Mumbai, June 22: Diversified firm Aditya Birla Nuvo has allotted Rs 1.85 crore convertible warrants to promoter group firms on a preferential basis to mop up over Rs 1,000 crore.                                                                                                                           
